$2,800!

02:53.882 --> 02:55.592
I can't

02:53.882 --> 02:55.592
believe you!

02:55.634 --> 02:57.218
You went behind my back,

02:57.260 --> 02:58.887
you spent money you had

02:57.260 --> 02:58.887
no right to spend to buy a pile

02:58.929 --> 03:00.430
of lumber

02:58.929 --> 03:00.430
and tubes.

03:00.472 --> 03:01.932
Don't worry.

03:01.974 --> 03:04.101
It has very detailed

03:01.974 --> 03:04.101
assembly instructions,

03:04.143 --> 03:07.896
which I won't go anywhere near

03:04.143 --> 03:07.896
because Malcolm's doing it.

03:07.938 --> 03:08.772
I don't mind.

03:20.283 --> 03:22.327
The baby's head

03:20.283 --> 03:22.327
was in the sun.

03:23.286 --> 03:25.246
Otto, what are you doing?

03:25.288 --> 03:27.124
I am posting

03:25.288 --> 03:27.124
the new safety rules.

03:27.166 --> 03:29.877
There have been far

03:27.166 --> 03:29.877
too many senseless accidents.

03:29.918 --> 03:33.172
People will have

03:29.918 --> 03:33.172
no excuse not to be safe.

03:33.212 --> 03:34.589
(hammering)

03:39.970 --> 03:42.514
(hammering continues)

03:52.315 --> 03:54.401
(gasping)

03:56.820 --> 04:00.281
Francis! You wouldn't believe

03:56.820 --> 04:00.281
what happened-- I almost...

04:00.323 --> 04:02.242
(thunder cracks)

04:04.536 --> 04:06.121
Otto! Oh, my God!

04:06.163 --> 04:07.956
You okay?!

04:11.126 --> 04:13.754
Manfred Schmidt.

04:15.172 --> 04:16.590
Did I tell you?

04:16.631 --> 04:18.884
You just can't have

04:16.631 --> 04:18.884
a care in the world

04:18.926 --> 04:20.301
when you're in a hot tub.

04:20.343 --> 04:23.138
It's like a trip back

04:20.343 --> 04:23.138
to the old amniotic sac.

04:23.180 --> 04:24.472
(door opening)

04:24.514 --> 04:26.558
Jamie's going to be

04:24.514 --> 04:26.558
asleep for another hour.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.309
Do you think

04:26.600 --> 04:28.309
I could borrow your car

04:28.351 --> 04:29.895
for a quick trip

04:28.351 --> 04:29.895
to the Lucky Aide?

04:29.937 --> 04:31.521
I'll drive!

04:31.563 --> 04:33.314
Oh, no, I'll be

04:31.563 --> 04:33.314
fine, really.

04:33.356 --> 04:34.482
You all look

04:33.356 --> 04:34.482
so comfortable,

04:34.524 --> 04:35.525
and it's really

04:34.524 --> 04:35.525
just...

04:35.567 --> 04:36.484
Not a problem at all.

04:36.526 --> 04:37.819
I got the keys. Let's go!

04:40.363 --> 04:42.116
Honey, take a load off.

04:42.157 --> 04:43.324
No, thanks.

04:43.366 --> 04:44.576
Since now

04:43.366 --> 04:44.576
you've decided

04:44.618 --> 04:45.577
we're a family

04:44.618 --> 04:45.577
where everyone

04:45.619 --> 04:46.620
does whatever

04:45.619 --> 04:46.620
they want,

04:46.661 --> 04:47.621
what I want is to

04:47.662 --> 04:49.957
not be in the hot tub.

04:50.665 --> 04:52.333
These jets are great.

04:52.375 --> 04:53.710
I couldn't hear

04:52.375 --> 04:53.710
a word she said.

04:53.752 --> 04:54.628
(door closes)

04:54.669 --> 04:56.713
And if you

04:54.669 --> 04:56.713
really listen,

04:56.755 --> 04:58.715
everything has

04:56.755 --> 04:58.715
its own vibration.

04:58.757 --> 05:00.341
The trees and the grass...

05:00.383 --> 05:01.969
I mean, it's like

05:00.383 --> 05:01.969
the whole world

05:02.010 --> 05:03.178
is screaming sometimes.

05:03.220 --> 05:04.763
But you know, you can

05:03.220 --> 05:04.763
get one of those

05:04.805 --> 05:07.348
white noise machines

05:04.805 --> 05:07.348
and really crank it...

05:07.390 --> 05:08.516
Oh, stop here.

05:08.558 --> 05:09.810
What about the drugstore?

05:09.851 --> 05:11.352
I just need

05:09.851 --> 05:11.352
to grab something.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.360
This is cool. I get to drive.

05:19.402 --> 05:21.196
Plus, I got to know

05:19.402 --> 05:21.196
Polly a little bit better.

05:21.238 --> 05:24.365
It turns out she hasn't

05:21.238 --> 05:24.365
had a TV in 12 years,

05:24.407 --> 05:27.368
and instead of chemicals,

05:24.407 --> 05:27.368
her dry cleaner uses tea.

05:27.410 --> 05:30.371
Okay, but the driving

05:27.410 --> 05:30.371
is still cool.

05:30.413 --> 05:31.372
Go! Go! Go! Go!

05:30.413 --> 05:31.372
What?

05:31.414 --> 05:33.292
I said go!

05:33.333 --> 05:34.668
(tires squealing)

05:34.709 --> 05:35.836
(shrieks)

05:43.051 --> 05:44.636
What did you do?

05:43.051 --> 05:44.636
Malcolm, just give me

05:43.051 --> 05:44.636
a second to explain.

05:44.678 --> 05:46.013
I didn't

05:44.678 --> 05:46.013
do anything wrong.

05:46.054 --> 05:48.389
Trust me--

05:46.054 --> 05:48.389
we're not in any danger.

05:48.431 --> 05:50.058
Then take your foot off the gas!

05:52.227 --> 05:54.604
(panting)

05:54.646 --> 05:56.064
Okay, what

05:54.646 --> 05:56.064
did you take?

05:56.106 --> 05:57.107
What is that thing?

05:57.149 --> 05:58.317
This is mine.

05:58.357 --> 06:00.068
It belongs to me.

06:00.110 --> 06:03.071
My ex-boyfriend Danny took it

06:00.110 --> 06:03.071
and he wouldn't give it back,

06:03.113 --> 06:04.823
and this happens

06:03.113 --> 06:04.823
to be my mother.

06:04.865 --> 06:05.991
Your what?

06:06.033 --> 06:07.575
My mother's in here.

06:06.033 --> 06:07.575
Her ashes.

06:07.617 --> 06:09.410
I meant to get her a nicer urn,

06:09.452 --> 06:12.413
but they just raised my tuition

06:09.452 --> 06:12.413
at the Wicca School.

06:12.455 --> 06:14.791
So why couldn't you just

06:12.455 --> 06:14.791
ask the guy for the ashes?

06:14.833 --> 06:16.293
I don't think that would be

06:16.335 --> 06:18.003
a really good route

06:16.335 --> 06:18.003
to go with Danny.

06:18.045 --> 06:19.629
He's a very troubled man.

06:19.671 --> 06:22.632
What?

06:19.671 --> 06:22.632
Please don't tell

06:19.671 --> 06:22.632
your parents, okay?

06:22.674 --> 06:25.593
I need you to keep

06:22.674 --> 06:25.593
this between us, please?

06:25.635 --> 06:26.511
I love Jamie,

06:26.553 --> 06:28.222
and he loves me,

06:28.263 --> 06:30.640
and I'd be crushed

06:28.263 --> 06:30.640
if I couldn't see him.

06:30.682 --> 06:32.433
Literally.

06:32.475 --> 06:35.270
Emotions can

06:32.475 --> 06:35.270
compress organs, Malcolm.

06:35.312 --> 06:37.480
So can you help me out on this?

06:37.522 --> 06:39.482
Fine.

06:39.524 --> 06:41.318
This is weird.

06:41.360 --> 06:42.652
All I keep thinking is,

06:42.694 --> 06:45.655
it is so cool

06:42.694 --> 06:45.655
that I'm driving.

06:45.697 --> 06:47.699
Francis, have

06:45.697 --> 06:47.699
you seen Otto?

06:47.741 --> 06:49.076
What's the matter?

06:49.117 --> 06:50.952
I don't like letting

06:49.117 --> 06:50.952
him out of my sight.

06:50.994 --> 06:52.453
He's been

06:50.994 --> 06:52.453
so accident-prone.

06:52.495 --> 06:55.123
In the past few days,

06:52.495 --> 06:55.123
he smashed up both our cars.

06:55.165 --> 06:56.875
He keeps falling down

06:55.165 --> 06:56.875
the stairs.

06:56.917 --> 06:58.668
This morning,

06:56.917 --> 06:58.668
he set his hair on fire

06:58.710 --> 07:00.503
with his reading glasses.

07:00.545 --> 07:02.547
Gretchen, my love,

07:00.545 --> 07:02.547
I wonder if you can

07:02.589 --> 07:04.091
fetch the tweezers.

07:04.132 --> 07:06.927
I seem to have an

07:04.132 --> 07:06.927
ass-full of cactus.

07:06.968 --> 07:09.470
Otto, it was just

07:06.968 --> 07:09.470
beginning to heal.

07:09.512 --> 07:12.557
Well, I'm sorry. It's not like

07:09.512 --> 07:12.557
I'm doing this on purpose.

07:12.599 --> 07:13.892
Ooh...

07:13.934 --> 07:14.893
Francis, I'm afraid

07:14.935 --> 07:16.353
I'm doing this on purpose.

07:16.395 --> 07:17.478
What,

07:16.395 --> 07:17.478
hurting yourself?

07:17.520 --> 07:18.939
I don't know.

07:17.520 --> 07:18.939
It doesn't seem

07:18.980 --> 07:21.482
like all of these things

07:18.980 --> 07:21.482
could be accidents.

07:21.524 --> 07:23.068
It's like

07:21.524 --> 07:23.068
there is some

07:23.110 --> 07:25.987
subconscious drive to punish

07:23.110 --> 07:25.987
myself for some unknown...

07:26.029 --> 07:27.114
(screams)

07:27.155 --> 07:29.490
(straining)

07:29.532 --> 07:32.577
Otto, what does the name

07:29.532 --> 07:32.577
Manfred Schmidt mean to you?

07:32.619 --> 07:35.496
I haven't thought

07:32.619 --> 07:35.496
about him for years.

07:35.538 --> 07:38.666
I'm... oh, oh...

07:38.708 --> 07:39.960
What?

07:40.001 --> 07:42.796
Manfred Schmidt

07:40.001 --> 07:42.796
is Gretchen's fiancé.

07:42.837 --> 07:46.174
Well, he was, until I stole her.

07:46.216 --> 07:47.508
You stole Gretchen?

07:47.550 --> 07:49.510
He was my best friend,

07:49.552 --> 07:51.805
but I was in love

07:49.552 --> 07:51.805
with Gretchen, too.

07:51.846 --> 07:52.806
And on the day

07:52.847 --> 07:54.515
they were going to elope,

07:54.557 --> 07:58.437
I told Manfred that

07:54.557 --> 07:58.437
Gretchen had already gone

07:58.478 --> 08:01.731
and that she would meet him

07:58.478 --> 08:01.731
at the train station in Berlin.

08:01.773 --> 08:03.024
Oh, Otto.

08:03.066 --> 08:04.943
Poor Gretchen stood

08:03.066 --> 08:04.943
in the rain for hours,

08:04.985 --> 08:05.986
devastated.

08:06.027 --> 08:07.321
And then

08:06.027 --> 08:07.321
I came along

08:07.362 --> 08:09.530
and I comforted her, and, uh,

08:09.572 --> 08:11.741
one thing led

08:09.572 --> 08:11.741
to another thing, and, uh...

08:11.783 --> 08:15.620
well, here we are--

08:11.783 --> 08:15.620
25 years of perfect love...

08:15.662 --> 08:17.747
built on a lie.

08:17.789 --> 08:19.958
Otto, this is obviously

08:17.789 --> 08:19.958
tearing you up inside.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.336
Why don't you just call

08:20.000 --> 08:22.336
this guy and apologize

08:22.377 --> 08:24.421
before you really

08:22.377 --> 08:24.421
end up hurting yourself?

08:24.463 --> 08:26.047
Francis, I don't think

08:24.463 --> 08:26.047
I have the courage.

08:26.089 --> 08:27.466
Besides,

08:27.507 --> 08:29.843
now that I know

08:27.507 --> 08:29.843
what is behind it,

08:29.884 --> 08:32.387
maybe the problem will go away.

08:33.596 --> 08:35.307
Those are thumb tacks.

08:36.599 --> 08:38.143
DEWEY:

08:36.599 --> 08:38.143
Dad.

08:38.185 --> 08:40.395
Noah and I were supposed

08:38.185 --> 08:40.395
to play together,

08:40.437 --> 08:41.855
but when I got

08:40.437 --> 08:41.855
to his house,

08:41.896 --> 08:43.482
he wasn't there.

08:43.523 --> 08:45.984
I waited for an hour,

08:43.523 --> 08:45.984
but he never showed up.

08:46.026 --> 08:47.568
Don't be so negative.

08:47.610 --> 08:50.489
Maybe he got hurt and was

08:47.610 --> 08:50.489
taken to the hospital,

08:50.530 --> 08:52.407
or maybe

08:50.530 --> 08:52.407
his grandmother died.

08:54.617 --> 08:56.828
NOAH:

08:54.617 --> 08:56.828
...and then my guy

08:54.617 --> 08:56.828
parachutes in

08:56.870 --> 08:58.621
and shoots your guy.

08:56.870 --> 08:58.621
(imitates gunfire)

08:58.663 --> 09:00.081
Oh! I'm cold!

09:00.123 --> 09:01.582
I'm so cold!

09:01.624 --> 09:03.001
(laughing)

09:04.627 --> 09:05.586
LOIS:

09:04.627 --> 09:05.586
Oh, come on, Jamie.

09:05.628 --> 09:06.796
Here comes the airplane.

09:06.838 --> 09:08.089
Come on, say "ah."

09:08.131 --> 09:09.590
Boy, you know,

09:08.131 --> 09:09.590
I think the tension

09:09.632 --> 09:11.510
in my neck

09:09.632 --> 09:11.510
was dulling my taste buds.

09:11.551 --> 09:12.802
These hamburgers

09:11.551 --> 09:12.802
are amazing, honey.

09:12.844 --> 09:14.012
Well, thank you.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.430
And even with the cheese,

09:15.472 --> 09:17.307
it came in for less

09:15.472 --> 09:17.307
than $2,800.

09:17.349 --> 09:19.017
Who has the mustard?

09:19.059 --> 09:21.311
I don't know.

09:19.059 --> 09:21.311
Maybe Reese stole it.

09:21.353 --> 09:23.063
Like he steals everything.

09:23.104 --> 09:24.981
Well, maybe the mustard

09:23.104 --> 09:24.981
likes me better.

09:25.023 --> 09:27.192
Maybe the mustard

09:25.023 --> 09:27.192
and I have more fun.

09:27.234 --> 09:28.860
You totally stole Noah from me!

09:28.902 --> 09:31.405
Whoa, you can't just

09:28.902 --> 09:31.405
change subjects on me.

09:31.446 --> 09:33.240
We were talking

